ges to a deterministic limit $\\theta_i \\in (\\lambda_+,1)$ determined by\n$t_i$. In this paper, we prove that these results hold universally under the\nsharp fourth moment conditions on the entries of $\\mathbf x$ and $\\mathbf y$.\nMoreover, we prove the results in full generality, in the sense that they also\nhold for near-degenerate $t_i$'s and for $t_i$'s that are close to the\nthreshold $t_c$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Feb 2021 17:09:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 8 Feb 2021 17:19:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 11 Jun 2022 16:18:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-14"}
